I work nights, sleep early day.  Sometimes I post, others I only read, and
yet at other times I find myself to agitated to think straight enough to post.
I find that all too often I am inclined to press or judge others for their innate
and unquestioning acceptance of various interpretations of ancient sprirtual
writings, and my presence then becomes an irritation or I am misconstrued
as being less than spiritual.  Actually, I find this a very tough place to hang
out, although for some reason it's compelling for me to see the often sad
clinging to religious dogma and how deeply it controls some people. Oddly,
those most affected seem to be the ones with the least 'Christian' attitude
(by teachings that I understand) or the least spiritual in words and actions.
It's difficult not to simply drop into large number of threads and accuse
certain posters of irrationality, but I know that I don't have the time to enter
a conversation for a long enough period to substantiate my feelings, nor
would it be worth the effort to attempt to alter dozens of years of apparent
brainwashing... and I will not resort to using the Bible as a foundation for
my arguments, which in the minds of most here would disqualify my
input.
